explains: vt. 超过；胜过；比……跑得快

sentences.en: This does not minimize the supremacy of their achievements, which outstrip our own as the sub-four-minute milers outstrip our jogging.
sentences.cn: 这并不会使他们的成就的优越性减少，他们的成就远胜过我们，就像不超过四分钟跑完一英里的运动员超过慢跑的我们一样。

sentences.en: Such enduring and intricately meshed levels of technical achievement outstrip by far anything achieved by our distant ancestors.
sentences.cn: 迄今为止，这种耐用且复杂的网状物的技术成就所达到的水平超越了我们远古祖先的任何一项成就。

sentences.en: Within the next few years, jobs will outstrip demand in some professions.
sentences.cn: 在以后的几年，一些职业会求大于供。
